{
  "text": "Proof. The results follows from the fact that the sequence ( 1 val (\u03a6)(\u0398 i )) i is a sub-martingale under \u03c4 \u03b5 and \u03c0. The following Lemma shows that the value-class qualitative \u03b5-optimal strategies for different value classes can be \"stitched\" or composed together to produce an \u03b5-optimal strategy. The key argument is as follows: if a play stays in S \\ (W 1 \u222a W 2 ) then by properties of value-class qualitative \u03b5-optimal strategies player 1 wins with probability 1; else the play reaches W 1 \u222a W 2 and then \u03b5-optimality is guaranteed by local \u03b5-optimality and Lemma 8. The details of the argument is similar to Lemma 14 in [CITATION_1] .",
